    "causal_summary": "The sk-doc HVR rules (`../../../skill/sk-doc/references/global/hvr_rules.md`) cover word-level and punctuation-level AI tells but lack structural patterns, section-level guidance and scoring calibration learned from writing production READMEs. The README template (`../../../skill/sk-doc/assets/documentation/readme_template.md`) is comprehensive but does not reflect patterns proven in the system-spec-kit exemplars (two-tier voice, numbered Feature subsections with `---` dividers, comparison tables, analogy patterns). There is no `../../../skill/sk-doc/references/specific/readme_creation.md` reference to guide the creation workflow the way `../../../skill/sk-doc/references/specific/install_guide_creation.md` guides install guide writing.",
